\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{n}K(y)\rightarrow\rho K(y)$
\end_inset

 and the continuity of the logarithm gives 
\begin_inset Formula $\log\rho K(y)\rightarrow\log\rho_{n}K(y)$
\end_inset

.
 The dominated convergence theorem gives 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left\lvert \int\mu(dy)\left[\log\rho K(y)-\log\rho_{n}K(y)\right]\right\rvert \rightarrow0.
\end{align*}

\end_inset

