 McKean-Vlasov SDEs present a dependence on the distribution 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{t}$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "mckean1966class"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 We follow the approach of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "bossy1997stochastic"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and consider 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 particles 
\begin_inset Formula $(X_{t}^{1},...,X_{t}^{N})$
\end_inset

 such that, at initialization, we sample i.i.d.
 particles 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{0}^{i}\sim\rho_{0}$
\end_inset

 and then they evolve according to the non-linear SDE 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
dX_{t}^{i,N}=\int\mu\left(dy\right)\frac{\nabla K(X_{t}^{i,N},y)}{\rho_{t}^{N}K(y)}dt+\sqrt{2\alpha}dW_{t}^{i},\quad\rho_{t}^{N}=\frac{1}{N}\sum_{i=1}^{N}\delta_{X_{t}^{i,N}}.\label{eq:nonlinearSDE_ip}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{t}^{i}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,\ldots,N$
\end_inset

 are 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 independent 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-dimensional standard Brownian motions and 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{t}^{N}$
\end_inset

 is the empirical measure given by the 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 particles.
 Existence and uniqueness of a solution of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:nonlinearSDE_ip"

\end_inset

 is given in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after "Theorem 7, page 253"
key "protter2005stochastic"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after "Theorem 3"
key "jourdain2007nonlinear"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 show that over a finite time interval 
\begin_inset Formula $[0,T]$
\end_inset

